

=Definition=

"Self-Provisioning is the “consumption” side of autonomous production ― the use of a good or service by the person or group who produced it. Examples include subsistence farming, medical selfcare, and fix-it-yourself practices."
(http://jasecon.wik.is/Consumption%2f%2fUse/Self-Provisioning)


